  <h1>Too Smart To Understand</h1>
  <time datetime=2014-04-11T21:31:45Z class="post-date">Fri, Apr 11, 2014</time>
  <p>Here is a meme I would very much like to see die forever. I&#8217;ll be reading book reviews and come across people gushing about how great the book was &#8212; and they know it&#8217;s great because they couldn&#8217;t understand any of it.</p>

<blockquote>
<p>In &#8220;Greatly Exaggerated&#8221; he is so fucking smart that I couldn&#8217;t even read the essay, because I am not, and never will be, his intellectual equal.</p>

<p><span id=&#8221;quote-attribute&#8221;>â€”from a review of <em>A Supposedly Fun Thing I&#8217;ll Never Do Again: Essays and Arguments</em></span></p>
</blockquote>

<p>So many 5 star reviews describe a book as incomprehensible.</p>

<p>I want to shake them. You&#8217;ve been tricked! Intelligence isn&#8217;t about hiding your ideas in an impenetrable shroud! It&#8217;s about laying insights bare so that anyone can understand them. Great writing is a combination of interdisciplinary mastery and clarity.</p>

<p>Where do people get this notion of intelligence-as-obfuscation from, anyways?</p>

